feature/v2-http-fast 2026-07-11
agent: claude (lucky-perch)
status: DONE (merged to main, hf-1..hf-5)
scope: NEW super-optimal v2 native JVM HTTP/WS plugin (Sergiy-directed) + v2 VM thread-safety.
result:
  hf-1: both v2 globals maps (Compiler.compileWithGlobals + Emit.globalsRef) -> concurrent
        TrieMap (race-free @-global first-touch under parallel handlers). GlobalsConcurrencyTest.
  hf-2: new module v2/runtime/std/http-fast-plugin (v2NativeHttpFastPlugin, id 50-http):
        FastHttpServer (blocking ServerSocket + vthread-per-conn), HttpProtocol (HTTP/1.1
        parser: content-length+chunked, expect-continue, caps, keep-alive), Router (:param/*
        + 404/405), NioNativeHttpServerHost (9-field Request, params in form, cookies).
        1.46x req/s vs raw com.sun.
  hf-3: WebSocketFrames (RFC 6455) + WsConnection (read loop, fragmentation, close handshake,
        thread-safe writes) + upgrade in FastHttpServer + WsChannel (server+client) + ws value
        tagged methods + onWebSocket/onWebSocketAuth/wsConnect/WsRoom.
  hf-4: use (middleware chain), cors, useGzip, sse/streamResponse (engine stream hook + HttpStream).
  hf-5: CLI now bundles the fast plugin instead of the old; old module v2/runtime/std/http-plugin
        REMOVED (tests ported). 40 module tests. e2e validated via `ssc run --native`.
LANE NOTE: fast plugin = v2 NATIVE http server (--native). --v2 FrontendBridge still uses the
  v1 WebServer (PluginBridge.registerWebServer) — separate seam, out of scope.
